article.description: Bo Hodges had a career-high 27 points as East Tennessee State topped Chattanooga 75-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Hodges carries E. Tennessee St. past Chattanooga 75-64
article.linkText: Hodges carries E. Tennessee St. past Chattanooga 75-64
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Bo Hodges had a career-high 27 points as East Tennessee State topped Chattanooga 75-64 on Saturday. Daivien Williamson had 15 points for East Tennessee State (18-3, 7-1 Southern Conference), which earned its fifth consecutive win. Lucas N'Guessan added 12 points. Ramon Vila had 17 points for the Mocs (13-8, 4-4). A.J. Caldwell added 17 points and seven rebounds. East Tennessee State plays Mercer at home on Wednesday. Chattanooga takes on Samford on the road on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
